      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "HARA'S PEST (3) is struggling to break through but racing consistently, finishing in the minors three starts on end. Last time out flew the lids with a fast early sectional but gathered in and finished in the minors when third (23.74) at Rockhampton over 407m. Has a strong record from box 3, including two wins. Racing well and deserves a win. LENARD CLYDE (2) was below best at his last start when 8th at Rockhampton following a second place finish (29.97) there two back. Has a good record here at this journey. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Key runner on best form. TOTAL FRANKY (6) is long overdue for a win and in super consistent form, jumping from this box to place last time at this track (21.84), making it three straight minors. Harder here but expected to measure up. HARA'S BLUEY (7) won by a wide margin last start. Big chance on that form.",
